Description: Reset errno before reading cdb_init.d
Author: OpenAI Codex
Forwarded: not-yet
Last-Update: 2026-04-19

`readdir()` leaves errno unchanged when it reaches end-of-directory.
On newer glibc releases, earlier `clone3()` fallback paths can leave
errno set to `ENOSYS`, which makes initdb misreport a successful
directory scan as:

  error while reading cdb_init.d directory: Function not implemented

Clear errno before the scan so the post-loop check only sees real
directory I/O errors.

--- a/src/bin/initdb/initdb.c
+++ b/src/bin/initdb/initdb.c
@@ -2022,6 +2022,7 @@ static void
 
 	/* Collect all files with .sql suffix in array. */
 	nscripts = 0;
+	errno = 0;
 	while ((file = readdir(dir)) != NULL)
 	{
 		int			namelen = strlen(file->d_name);
